THE NMB MastaBata ‘Kivyakovyako’ campaign has entered the fifth week with 100 winners being picked and walking away with 10m/- cash prizes. The 5th draw of the NMB MastaBata campaign held in Dar es Salaam Thursday was witnessed by President of MasterCard International, Sub Saharan Africa Mark Elliott. NMB Card Centre Manager Sophia Mwamwitwa said last year, MasterCard which is the NMB business partner awarded the bank a top prize for promoting the use of cards to customers for making various payments. “Apart from witnessing the 5th draw of NMB MastaBata campaign, President Elliot commended the bank for running a successful MastaBata campaign to promote the use of cards,” she said. She said also that the MasterCard International, Sub Saharan Africa President visited the bank to learn various services offered as well as managerial operations. A total of 525 winners have been awarded 75m/- since the 10 weeks campaign to drive up the use of Mastercard, Mastapass QR and Point of Sale (PoS) was launched last year. “This campaign aims to encourage and motivate our customers and all Tanzanians, in general, to use NMB Mastercard and Mastercard QR when making payments and in their internet banking transactions,” she said. During the three months of the NMB MastaBata Kivyako Vyako promotion, more than 1,000 NMB customers will win the over 200m/-lender has set aside for spur card usage. She said apart from weekly raffles, there will be also monthly winners and a grand finale of the competition in March. Two monthly raffles will be held during the campaign to pick the 25 winners of 1m/- each. NMB Bank Plc has been running the MastaBata campaign series since 2018 to principally promote the nascent local digital economy and support national efforts to make Tanzania a casheless society. The lender is also using the campaigns to reward loyal customers who have transformed together with it in its digital transformation journey. Moreover, NMB is using the investment that has equally helped to advance e-commerce in the country to lure new customers for consolidating its market leadership status.